>> Note: DON'T add tomato paste to the sauce. You'll want to. But it is not the move.

Press the @tofu{1 block} thoroughly.

Cut into 6-8 slabs and set aside. 

Preheat a #frying pan{} over medium heat.

In a small pot add @BBQ sauce{}, @worchestershire sauce{}, @sesame oil{}, @soy sauce{}, @brown sugar{}, @sriracha{}, @black pepper{}, and combine over low heat. 

Salt the slabs and fry in @neutral oil{} until crispy. 

Remove the tofu, coat each piece in the sauce, and enjoy!
